data.title: Mehr News Agency
data.text:
World's greatest feast of love underway in deserts of Iraq

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The World's biggest feast is annually held in the Iraqi deserts in the month of Safar (the second month of the lunar-based Islamic calendar) with participating millions of people of all religions and nations.

Israeli warplanes target own troops in south Gaza

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Israeli warplane mistakenly killed Zionist trooper, injures 6 others during airstrike in southern Gaza on Monday.

3 Pakistani soldiers, 5 terrorists killed at Afghan border

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Three Pakistani soldiers were killed and five terrorists were killed as the Pakistani security forces foiled an infiltration attempt at the Pakistan-Afghanistan border in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa’s Bajaur district.

Death toll from central China downpours rises to 50

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – At least 50 people were confirmed dead on Monday following search and rescue efforts after torrential rain lashed central China in late July, state media said.

VIDEO: Foreign pilgrims at Iran’s Chazabeh Border in Arbaeen

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Foreign pilgrims can only enter Iraq from the Chazabeh Border Crossing and Iranian Mawkibs are serving these foreign pilgrims on their way to the holy shrines in Karbala during Arabeen walk.

Turkey's foreign ministry:

Netanyahu's cabinet should be tried for genocide in Gaza

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The Turkish Foreign Ministry called for an international tribunal for the Zionist regime's cabinet for the continuation of the genocidal war in Gaza.

Lebanon lodges complaint to UNSC against Zionist regime

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The Lebanon’s Ministry of Foreign Affairs announced that it has filed a complaint against the Zionist regime to the United Nations Security Council (UNSC) regarding the breaking of sound barrier in Lebanese sky.

By: Somayeh Noori

Khosravi border parking lots during Arbaeen procession

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – There are 15 parking lots on the Khosravi border terminal with a capacity of 200,000 cars for the Arbaeen pilgrimage.

PA chief 'Mahmoud Abbas' to visit Gaza after 17 years

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Head of the Palestinian Authority (PA) Mahmoud Abbas wants to visit Gaza Strip after 17 years following the movements and contacts in the regional and international levels.

US delivers different weapons, ammunitions to Tel Aviv

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – In line with its efforts to create a protective belt for the occupying regime of Israel against missiles and drones of Iran and Hezbollah, the US delivers advanced planes and missiles to Zionist regime to ward off any attack.

Hezbollah hit Israeli Margaliot settlement with rockets

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The rocket attack on the Israeli Margaliot settlement located in the north of the occupied territories has caused damage to the Zionists.

Hezbollah kills high-ranking Israeli officer

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Lebanese Hezbollah Resistance movement says its forces have killed a high-ranking Zionist regime's military's officer in drone strike on Ya'ara, northwestern occupied Palestine.

By: Iman Hamikhah

Journalists embark on "Rahina-e-Pishraft" tour in Hamedan

HAMEDAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The Rahian-e-Pishraft (Passengers of Progress) tour was held in Hamedan on Sunday at the initiative taken by the provincial Industry, Mine and Trade Organization.

By: Ali Haddadi Asl

3rd session of reviewing qualifications of proposed ministers

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The third day of reviewing the qualifications of the ministers proposed by President Masoud Pezeshkian in the 14th government was held in the Iranian parliament on Monday.

Israeli army admits soldier killed in Hezbollah drone attack

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – An Israeli soldier was killed in a Hezbollah drone attack on the Western Galilee this morning, the military of the Zionist regime announced.

Putin says ‘would be happy’ to facilitate Baku-Yerevan peace

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Russia “would be happy to” facilitate the signing of a peace treaty between the two neighbors Armenia and Azerbaijan, President Vladimir Putin said during talks with his Azerbaijani counterpart on Monday.

Ex-Saudi official claims;

MBS ‘forged father’s signature’ to authorize war on Yemen

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Saudi Arabia’s Crown Prince and de-facto ruler, Mohammed Bin Salman (MBS), allegedly forged his father King Salman’s signature to deploy ground troops to Yemen, a former royal adviser has claimed.

EU warns humanitarian crisis deepening in Gaza, West Bank

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The European Union has warned of deepening humanitarian crisis in the besieged Gaza Strip and the occupied West Bank, amid Israel’s ongoing genocide against Palestinians.

US, S Korea begin military drills to strengthen their defense

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – The US and South Korea begin military drills aimed at strengthening their defense against North Korea.

VIDEO: Watch violation of human rights in Germany

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Footage shows German police violently attacking a pro-Palestine protester before arresting her for calling for an end to the Israeli genocide in Gaza.

China's State Council premier to visit Russia on August 20

TEHRAN, Aug. 19 (MNA) – Premier of the State Council of China Li Qiang will visit Russia on August 20-22 at the invitation of Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin, the Russian Cabinet press service reported.
